                           --AMIGADOS GUIDE V2.6--
                                    SAY


   USE:
   This command provides access to the Amigas built in speech facility.

   PATH:
   SYS:Utilities

   SYSTEM:
   2.0, 2.1, 3.0

   EXAMPLES:
   1>SAY
   1>SAY Welcome to ADOS Guide
   1>SAY Welcome to ADOS Guide -f
   1>SAY -x S:Startup-sequence

   NOTES:
   After you have typed the example above you must then type in what you
   want the computer to say. As in example 2.

   By attaching the following options you can customise the voice to your
   tastes.(see example 3 above)

   m  Use male voice.
   f  Use female voice.
   r  Use Robotic voice.
   s  change the speed at which the speaker attempts to read the text.
      (40...400)
   p  Change the pitch frequency. (65...320)
   x  Say will attempt to read and speak text from a specified file.
      (see example 4 above)

   Please note that Workbench 3.X does not come with the command SAY but
   the capability is still there.
